-- Summary 1: Added concrete Runway resource (Runway1, Runway2) to represent runways and satisfy scalability constraint.
-- Summary 2: Fixed type errors: replaced incorrect usage of Interface atoms (Runway_Timetable_UI, Runway_API, Flight_Database) as Resource targets with proper Runway resource references and channel membership checks.
-- Summary 3: Corrected predicates and assertions to use 'some c: op.channel | c.kind = ...' instead of type-mismatched 'UI in op.channel'.
-- Summary 4: Model now structurally consistent and checkable without type errors.
-- Assumption 1: Runways are the primary resources; we added two instances to meet the scalability fact (#Resource >= 2).
-- Assumption 2: Flight details are accessed via Flight_Database interface; time slots are not explicitly modeled, but edge case assertions abstractly capture safety.
-- Assumption 3: All runway resources are owned by Air_Traffic_Controllers and accessible to Air_Traffic_Controllers and Operations_Management, consistent with typical roles.
-- Open issue 1: Edge cases about time slot overlapping are modeled abstractly via permission equivalence; no explicit slot data structure exists.
-- Open issue 2: Non-functional requirements are approximated with structural constraints (e.g., channel count) that may not fully capture performance/availability semantics.
-- Open issue 3: Security requirements are empty; no additional security assertions added.


